"       Type I: \"M&uuml;llerian\" agenesis or hypoplasia",
"      </td>",
"     </tr>",
"     <tr>",
"      <td>",
"       A. Vaginal (uterus may be normal or exhibit a variety of malformations)",
"      </td>",
"     </tr>",
"     <tr>",
"      <td>",
"       B. Cervical",
"      </td>",
"     </tr>",
"     <tr>",
"      <td>",
